# .dockerignore — controls what `docker build` sends from the build
# context to the daemon. Smaller context = faster `make image` and a
# tighter blast radius for accidental file leaks into the image.
#
# We exclude:
#   - dist/: build output of `make build` — must be regenerated inside
#     the builder stage from a clean slate (spec FR-4 step 1).
#   - .sync-workdir/: maintainer-only sync conflict workdir.
#   - .git/: not needed by the builder; upstream's pyproject.toml uses
#     plain setuptools, no setuptools-scm, so no git metadata is read
#     during `pip install -e .`. Skipping .git/ shaves megabytes off
#     the build context.
#   - .shepherd/smoke-run-*.log: ephemeral milestone smoke-run logs.
#   - Python / editor / OS noise.
#
# We INTENTIONALLY keep:
#   - upstream/, patches/, overlay/, tools/, scripts/, nadia-rename.yaml,
#     Makefile: required by the builder stage's `make build`.
#   - .shepherd/spec.md, plan.md, standards.md, progress.md: tiny;
#     harmless if they end up in the builder context. Stripped from the
#     runtime stage by the FR-7 "copy ONLY dist/nadia/" rule.
#   - README.md, AGENTS.md, .gitattributes, .gitignore: tiny; same as
#     above.

# --- Build outputs (regenerated by make build) ---
dist/
.sync-workdir/

# --- Git metadata (not consumed by the builder) ---
.git/

# --- Quilt state (transient; created inside the builder) ---
.pc/
.quilt/
*.rej
*.orig

# --- Per-milestone smoke-run logs ---
.shepherd/smoke-run-*.log

# --- Python artefacts ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.venv/
*.egg-info/

# --- Editor / OS noise ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store

# --- Local env files (never image them) ---
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
